Process called "create_mock_proximity_sensor" returns Sensor:
    Return Sensor with:
    sensor_id as "proximity_0"
    sensor_name as "Proximity Sensor"
    sensor_type as "proximity"
    vendor as "Generic"
    version as 1
    power_consumption as 0.5
    maximum_range as 5.0
    resolution as 5.0
    min_delay as 0
    max_delay as 0
    is_available as true
    requires_permission as false

Process called "get_latest_sensor_reading" that takes sensor as Sensor returns SensorReading:
    Note: Platform-specific sensor reading
    Return SensorReading with:
    sensor_id as sensor.sensor_id
    timestamp as DateTime.now()
    values as create_mock_sensor_values with sensor_type as sensor.sensor_type
    accuracy as "medium"
    reading_id as generate_reading_id()

Process called "create_mock_sensor_values" that takes sensor_type as String returns List[Float]:
    Match sensor_type:
    When "accelerometer":
    Return list containing 0.1, 0.2, 9.8
    When "gyroscope":
    Return list containing 0.01, 0.02, 0.03
    When "magnetometer":
    Return list containing 20.0, 30.0, 40.0
    When "light":
    Return list containing 150.0
    When "proximity":
    Return list containing 3.0
    Otherwise:
    Return list containing 0.0